title: Nineteen Lincolns
description: portrait of bearded man dressed as President Lincoln; mole on PR cheek; man seated with PR hand resting on PR thigh and PL arm resting across PL thigh; blurry trees and blue sky in distance; framed behind glass in black wood frame; one of a set of 18 photographs to be displayed together
creditline: The Shirley Mahowald and Henry Kinsell Endowment for Art Acquisition
